criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All the patients met the diagnosis of COPD according to Global Initiative for Chronic
             Obstructive Lung Disease (GOLD) guidelines and had definite airflow limitation with a
             post-bronchodilator forced expiratory volume in 1 second (FEV1) / forced vital
             capacity (FVC)<0.7.

          -  They were admitted to the ward of Department of Respiratory and Critical Care Medicine
             due to COPD exacerbation.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  age <40 years;

          -  subjects with airway diseases other than COPD;

          -  comunity acquired pneumonia;

          -  active tuberculosis;

          -  severe liver or renal dysfunction;

          -  malignancy;

          -  HIV infection or immunodeficiency;

          -  ever received glucocorticoid in the past month.
